http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Floral-tributes-paid-to-Lal-Bahadur-Shastri/article13994844.ece

Leader of the Congress in the Lok Sabha M. Mallikarjun Kharge paid floral tributes to the former Prime Minister Lal Bahadur Shastri on the late leader’s 50th death anniversary here on Monday.Mr. Kharge said that the former Prime Minister had played a heroic role and exhibited his leadership qualities during the India-Pakistan war in 1965; Shastri’s slogan of Jai Jawan Jai Kisan became very popular during the war and it is remembered even today.Shastri, who was influenced by Mahatma Gandhi’s ideology, became his follower. He was also a close aide of Pandit Jawarharlal Nehru. Shastri’s honesty and dedication towards his work had inspired many leaders.Stating that Shastri was sensitive to public issues, Mr. Kharge said, he [Shastri] had resigned as Minister for Railways in 1956 following train accidents in Andhra Pradesh and Tamil Nadu.The Congress has contributed to the uplift of the poor and the downtrodden sections of society, Mr. Kharge said.Instead of criticising, people who questioned the contribution of the party to the nation should study history, Mr. Kharge added.Minister of State for Medical Education Sharanprakash Patil, MLC Iqbal Ahmed Saradgi and president of the Kalaburagi District Congress Committee Baganagowda Patil Sunkanur were present.